== Introduction

This is alpha grade software.

Under active development.  But simple use cases may be worth checking out.

http://www.csie.ntu.edu.tw/~cjlin/libsvm/

libsvm version 310


== Installation

1.  Download 
2.  make lib
3.  place .so and .h in load path
4.  write friendly email to libsvm debian maintainer about version 3 (actually looks like some recent progress)  TODO update these instructions

gem install libsvmffi

== Usage

#> require 'libsvmffi'

#> m = Libsvmffi::Model.new
#> m.add :good, {:height => 1, :width => 1, :length => 1}
#> m.add :bad, {:height => 10, :width => 3, :length => 6}
#> m.train

#> m.classify({:height => 1, :width => 1.1, :length => 1})
#=> :good
